<div class="tribe-manual">
  <ManualHeader />

  <ManualPageNav @activePage="backend" />

  <div class="container pb-5">

    <div class="steps-container mb-5">

      <div class="step-card" data-step-name="Check Docker Installation verify docker version">
        <div class="step-header" onclick="toggleStep(this)">
          <span class="step-badge">1</span>
          <span class="step-title">Check Docker Installation</span>
          <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down step-chevron"></i>
        </div>
        <div class="step-body">
          <p>Verify Docker and Docker Compose are installed before proceeding:</p>
          <div class="row g-3">
            <div class="col-md-6">
              <div class="card method-item">
                <div class="card-body d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center">
                  <div><strong>Docker:</strong><br><code>docker --version</code></div>
                  <button class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-dark" onclick="copyCmd('docker --version', this)" type="button">Copy</button>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6">
              <div class="card method-item">
                <div class="card-body d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center">
                  <div><strong>Docker Compose:</strong><br><code>docker compose version</code></div>
                  <button class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-dark" onclick="copyCmd('docker compose version', this)" type="button">Copy</button>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="alert alert-warning mt-3 mb-0">
            <strong>Not installed?</strong> Go back to the Prerequisites page to install Docker, or visit <a href="https://www.docker.com/get-started/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">docker.com/get-started</a>.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step-card" data-step-name="Navigate to Project Directory backend docker-compose.yml">
        <div class="step-header" onclick="toggleStep(this)">
          <span class="step-badge">2</span>
          <span class="step-title">Navigate to Project Directory</span>
          <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down step-chevron"></i>
        </div>
        <div class="step-body">
          <p>Open your terminal and navigate to the directory containing your <code>docker-compose.yml</code> file:</p>
          <div class="command-block">
            <button class="btn btn-sm copy-btn-block" onclick="copyCmd('cd /path/to/your/project', this)" type="button">Copy</button>
            <code><span class="comment"># Replace with your actual project path</span><br>cd /path/to/your/project</code>
          </div>
          <div class="row g-3 mt-2">
            <div class="col-md-6">
              <div class="card method-item">
                <div class="card-body d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center">
                  <div><strong>Windows:</strong><br><code>cd C:\Users\YourName\Documents\MyProject</code></div>
                  <button class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-dark" onclick="copyCmd('cd C:\\Users\\YourName\\Documents\\MyProject', this)" type="button">Copy</button>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6">
              <div class="card method-item">
                <div class="card-body d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center">
                  <div><strong>macOS / Linux:</strong><br><code>cd ~/Documents/MyProject</code></div>
                  <button class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-dark" onclick="copyCmd('cd ~/Documents/MyProject', this)" type="button">Copy</button>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="alert alert-warning mt-3 mb-0">
            <strong>Important:</strong> Make sure you're in the directory that contains your <code>docker-compose.yml</code> file before running the next commands.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step-card" data-step-name="Configure environment env sample chown uploads logs www-data">
        <div class="step-header" onclick="toggleStep(this)">
          <span class="step-badge">3</span>
          <span class="step-title">Configure Environment</span>
          <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down step-chevron"></i>
        </div>
        <div class="step-body">
          <p>Create your <code>.env</code> from the sample, then fix ownership so the <code>php_tribe</code> container can write uploads and logs:</p>
          <div class="command-block mb-2">
            <button class="btn btn-sm copy-btn-block" onclick="copyCmd('cp .env.sample .env', this)" type="button">Copy</button>
            <code>cp .env.sample .env</code>
          </div>
          <div class="command-block">
            <button class="btn btn-sm copy-btn-block" onclick="copyCmd('chown www-data: uploads logs -R', this)" type="button">Copy</button>
            <code>chown www-data: uploads logs -R</code>
          </div>
          <div class="alert alert-warning mt-3 mb-0">
            <strong>Why this matters:</strong> Skipping <code>chown</code> causes <code>php_tribe</code> to crash with a misleading <code>array_diff(): Argument #1 ($array) must be of type array, false given</code> error in <code>Config.php</code>. The real cause is unwritable directories, not a type error.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step-card" data-step-name="Start Backend Junction Tribe API docker compose up build">
        <div class="step-header" onclick="toggleStep(this)">
          <span class="step-badge">4</span>
          <span class="step-title">Start Backend (Junction + Tribe API)</span>
          <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down step-chevron"></i>
        </div>
        <div class="step-body">
          <p>Start all backend services with Docker Compose:</p>
          <div class="command-block">
            <button class="btn btn-sm copy-btn-block" onclick="copyCmd('docker compose up -d --build', this)" type="button">Copy</button>
            <code>docker compose up -d --build</code>
          </div>

          <div class="alert alert-success mt-3">
            <h6 class="alert-heading mb-1">What this command does:</h6>
            <p class="mb-0"><code>up</code> starts the containers &bull; <code>-d</code> runs in background (detached) &bull; <code>--build</code> rebuilds images before starting</p>
          </div>

          <p class="mt-3 mb-1"><strong>For older Docker versions:</strong></p>
          <div class="command-block">
            <button class="btn btn-sm copy-btn-block" onclick="copyCmd('docker-compose up -d --build', this)" type="button">Copy</button>
            <code>docker-compose up -d --build</code>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step-card" data-step-name="Access Backend Services URLs Junction Tribe phpMyAdmin API endpoints ports">
        <div class="step-header" onclick="toggleStep(this)">
          <span class="step-badge">5</span>
          <span class="step-title">Access Backend Services</span>
          <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down step-chevron"></i>
        </div>
        <div class="step-body">
          <p>Once your backend is running, confirm the ports Docker published before opening services:</p>
          <div class="command-block mb-3">
            <button class="btn btn-sm copy-btn-block" onclick="copyCmd('node portmap', this)" type="button">Copy</button>
            <code><span class="comment"># Lists every container → host port mapping</span><br>node portmap</code>
          </div>
          <p>Then access the following services using the ports shown:</p>

          <h6 class="mt-3 mb-2">Main Services</h6>
          <div class="row g-3">
            <div class="col-md-6">
              <div class="service-link-card">
                <h6>Junction (Backend Management)</h6>
                <a href="http://junction.localhost:12002" target="_blank" class="d-block mb-1 font-monospace" rel="noopener noreferrer">http://junction.localhost:12002</a>
                <small class="text-muted">No-code backend service</small>
                <div class="mt-2"><strong>Credentials:</strong> Username: <code>junction</code> | Password: <code>password</code></div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6">
              <div class="service-link-card">
                <h6>Tribe Framework</h6>
                <a href="http://tribe.localhost:12000" target="_blank" class="d-block mb-1 font-monospace" rel="noopener noreferrer">http://tribe.localhost:12000</a>
                <small class="text-muted">Main Tribe Framework interface</small>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h6 class="mt-4 mb-2">Development Tools</h6>
          <div class="row g-3">
            <div class="col-md-6">
              <div class="service-link-card">
                <h6>Tribe APIs</h6>
                <a href="http://tribe.localhost:12000/api.php/webapp/0" target="_blank" class="d-block mb-1 font-monospace" rel="noopener noreferrer">http://tribe.localhost:12000/api.php/webapp/0</a>
                <small class="text-muted">RESTful API endpoints</small>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6">
              <div class="service-link-card">
                <h6>phpMyAdmin</h6>
                <a href="http://tribe.localhost:12000/phpmyadmin" target="_blank" class="d-block mb-1 font-monospace" rel="noopener noreferrer">http://tribe.localhost:12000/phpmyadmin</a>
                <small class="text-muted">Web interface for MySQL database management</small>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h6 class="mt-4 mb-2">Static Hosting &amp; Custom Code</h6>
          <div class="row g-3">
            <div class="col-md-4">
              <div class="service-link-card">
                <h6>Static / JAM Stack</h6>
                <a href="http://dist.localhost:12003" target="_blank" class="d-block mb-1 font-monospace" rel="noopener noreferrer">dist.localhost:12003</a>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4">
              <div class="service-link-card">
                <h6>Static + PHP</h6>
                <a href="http://dist-php.localhost:12004" target="_blank" class="d-block mb-1 font-monospace" rel="noopener noreferrer">dist-php.localhost:12004</a>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4">
              <div class="service-link-card">
                <h6>Custom PHP</h6>
                <a href="http://tribe.localhost:12000/custom/" target="_blank" class="d-block mb-1 font-monospace" rel="noopener noreferrer">tribe.localhost:12000/custom/</a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h6 class="mt-4 mb-2">Database</h6>
          <div class="service-link-card">
            <h6>Direct MySQL Access</h6>
            <span class="d-block mb-1 font-monospace text-muted">mysql.localhost:3306</span>
            <small class="text-muted">Use a MySQL client (not a browser)</small>
            <div class="mt-2"><strong>Connection:</strong> Host: <code>mysql.localhost</code> | Port: <code>3306</code> | Database: <code>tribe</code> | User: <code>root</code> | Password: <code>root</code></div>
          </div>

          <div class="alert alert-info mt-3 mb-0">
            <strong>Tip:</strong> All services use subdomain routing. If you're having trouble accessing them, ensure your system can resolve <code>*.localhost</code> domains. Most modern systems handle this automatically.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step-card" data-step-name="Stop Backend Services docker compose down restart logs">
        <div class="step-header" onclick="toggleStep(this)">
          <span class="step-badge">6</span>
          <span class="step-title">Stop Backend Services</span>
          <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down step-chevron"></i>
        </div>
        <div class="step-body">
          <p>When you want to stop and remove the containers:</p>
          <div class="command-block">
            <button class="btn btn-sm copy-btn-block" onclick="copyCmd('docker compose down', this)" type="button">Copy</button>
            <code>docker compose down</code>
          </div>

          <p class="mt-3 mb-1"><strong>For older Docker versions:</strong></p>
          <div class="command-block">
            <button class="btn btn-sm copy-btn-block" onclick="copyCmd('docker-compose down', this)" type="button">Copy</button>
            <code>docker-compose down</code>
          </div>

          <div class="alert alert-success mt-3 mb-0">
            <h6 class="alert-heading mb-1">Useful commands:</h6>
            <p class="mb-0">
              <code>docker-compose logs</code> &mdash; View logs &bull;
              <code>docker-compose ps</code> &mdash; List running containers &bull;
              <code>docker-compose restart</code> &mdash; Restart services
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <ManualFooter />

  </div>
</div>

<ManualScripts />
